abstract: Win, lose or draw, there’s no legitimacy in America anymore.
snippet: Win, lose or draw, there’s no legitimacy in America anymore.
lead_paragraph: I’ll let you in on a little secret about media coverage of prime-time political debates: What happens in the first half, even the first quarter, gets much more attention than what happens as the night drags on.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Friday said on Twitter that four candidates are under consideration for the job of U.S. intelligence chief and that a decision would come in the next few weeks.

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg, who was challenged at this week’s Democratic debate over the agreements, said the women had made complaints “about comments they said I had made.” His rivals said it wasn’t enough.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg, who was challenged at this week’s Democratic debate over the agreements, said the women had made complaints “about comments they said I had made.” His rivals said it wasn’t enough.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Michael R. Bloomberg said Friday that he was willing to release three women from nondisclosure agreements with his company so they could discuss their complaints about him publicly, reversing himself from his position at this week’s Democratic presidential debate when he came under fire from his rivals for resisting such a move.

abstract: The United States may give American farmers additional money until trade deals with China, Mexico, Canada and other countries fully go into effect, President Donald Trump said on Friday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Stephen E. Biegun was sworn in as deputy secretary of state, it was in front of an unusual crowd at the State Department — one that included loyalists to President Trump, but also a mix of Never Trumpers and Democrats.

abstract: Haunted by the 2016 death in Cairo of an Italian student, Giulio Regeni, Italians are campaigning for the release of an Egyptian who has said he was tortured.
snippet: Haunted by the 2016 death in Cairo of an Italian student, Giulio Regeni, Italians are campaigning for the release of an Egyptian who has said he was tortured.
lead_paragraph: CAIRO — When an Egyptian student was arrested at the Cairo Airport recently, it was hardly an unusual event. Egypt’s security services routinely detain human rights defenders, lawyers, academics and other government critics, most of whom vanish into prison for years. Many complain of torture.
